   "source": [
    "with open(r\"C:\\Users\\abrab\\Downloads\\sample_AAPL.txt\", \"r\") as f:\n",
    "    listItems = f.read().splitlines()  "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "085dae0e-bbe8-4cf9-83b5-0b439139cd56",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "appleprices = listItems\n",
    "for i in range(0, len(listItems)):\n",
    "    appleprices[i] = float(listItems[i]) "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "d47c0e76-9b9e-42c4-afba-69d70c097389",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [

      ]

     "output_type": "display_data"

   ],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# Convert the list of strings to a list of floats\n",
    "appleprices = [float(price) for price in listItems]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Generate the x-axis values (1 to 252)\n",
    "x_values = list(range(1, len(appleprices) + 1))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot the line graph\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))  # Set the figure size\n",
    "plt.plot(x_values, appleprices, color=\"blue\", label=\"Stock Price\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add title and labels\n",
    "plt.title(\"Apple Stock Price, Nov 2019 to Nov 2020\", fontsize=14)\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Day\", fontsize=12)\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Trading price\", fontsize=12)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add grid and legend\n",
    "plt.grid(True, linestyle=\"--\", alpha=0.7)\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Display the plot\n",
    "plt.show()\n"
   ]
  }
